      "writtenOn": "2020-10-17T21:49:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So there were a couple possibilities if there are no parent entities in datastore:\n\n1. Keep the hierarchy with the parent key. In this case, `Lookup` does an ancestor query to narrow down to a specific host/repo.\n\n2. Have no parent key, and have \"host/repo\" as a field in the model. In this case `Lookup` does a query filtering for equality on HostRepo. (And in this case the ID of the entity doesn\u0027t matter so much.)\n\nIs there any reason to believe that one of those queries is more performant than the other?",
      "parentUuid": "d991058e_fac45641",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 64
      },
      "revId": "1becb544168192f8dd2691e753d5dea190b3f760",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6944c35e_d5370fd0",
        "filename": "cv/internal/gerrit/gobmap/map.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 33,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-18T15:30:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The goal is fast reads by host/repo. Since there can be several, we want them to be located in close proximity, which means their IDs (\u003cparent keys\u003e + child ID) must be close to each other.\nSo, ID must be semantically (host,repo,project).\n\nWe can query based on .host_repo field, but this means datastore has to first check secondary index to get list of IDs and actually read the entities.\nIdeal query would just use the primary index: we need to get all records s.t.\n   id \u003e (host, repo, MIN)\n and\n   id \u003c (host, repo, MAX)\n\nwhere MIN,MAX are lexicographic boundaries.\n\n\nFinally, how to encode (host,repo,project) ID as a string while having easy MIN \u0026 MAX?\nIdeally, we shouldn\u0027t make assumptions on GoB / LUCI charsets (just in case these are relaxed later), but it\u0027s to assume they\u0027ll be \u003c 64KiB long each:\n\n4-byte hex-encoded host len\n\u003chost\u003e\n4-byte hex-encoded repo len\n\u003crepo\u003e\n4-byte hex-encoded LUCI project len\n\u003cproject\u003e\n\nThus, suitable MIN and MAX lexicographic boundaries are \"0000\" and \"FFFF\", respectively.\ne.g. searching for \"chromium.googlesource.com\" \"chromiumos\" repo would mean querying for \n  ID \u003e \"0019chromium.googlesource.com000Achromiumos0000\"\n  ID \u003c \"0019chromium.googlesource.com000AchromiumosFFFF\"\nwhich will find \n  ID \u003d \"0019chromium.googlesource.com000Achromiumos0008chromeos\" (aka LUCI project\u003dchromeos)\n\nAgree?",
      "parentUuid": "92c325cd_a6ef0fb2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 64
      },
      "revId": "1becb544168192f8dd2691e753d5dea190b3f760",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
